        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-24T18:49:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the downside of not using pointer is that each function call copies entire struct.\nthe reason \"none of the function is supposed to modify any value\" is generally not a reason to use raw struct receivers.\n\nyeah, I think we should change the code to use non-pointers. It results in somewhat weird code: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/2557151/comment/fe1b0fe8_2155f12d/",
      "parentUuid": "7d0e62d8_9ab450a6",
      "revId": "8c7b8843fb7b389719f9d1a7bf093e88791999f4",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1cc97e30_6f76b0bc",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
